{"_response_info":{"status":"ok"},"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/national-insurance-classes.json","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/national-insurance-classes","title":"National Insurance Classes","format":"answer","updated_at":"2012-11-08T16:16:05+00:00","details":{"need_id":"B686","business_proposition":true,"description":"Different classes of National Insurance contribution - what they are and who pays them","language":"en","body":"\n<div class=\"summary\">\n<p>The class you pay depends on your employment status or if you have a gap in your National Insurance record.</p>\n</div>\n\n<table>\n  <thead>\n    <tr>\n      <th>National Insurance class</th>\n      <th>Who pays this class?</th>\n    </tr>\n  </thead>\n  <tbody>\n    <tr>\n      <td>Class 1</td>\n      <td>Employees earning more than £146 a week and under state pension age - they&rsquo;re automatically deducted by your employer</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>Class 1A or 1B</td>\n      <td>Employers pay these directly themselves on their employee&rsquo;s expenses or benefits</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>Class 2</td>\n      <td>Self-employed people - you don&rsquo;t have to pay if you earn less than £5,595 and <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://search2.hmrc.gov.uk/kb5/hmrc/forms/view.page?record=yKpjabZqCc8&amp;formid=433\" title=\"Apply for Class 2 exemption\">get an exemption</a></td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>Class 3</td>\n      <td>Voluntary contributions - you can pay them to fill or avoid gaps in your National insurance record</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>Class 4</td>\n      <td>Self-employed people earning more than £7,605</td>\n    </tr>\n  </tbody>\n</table>\n\n","alternative_title":""},"tags":[{"title":"Business Link","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/businesslink.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":null,"short_description":null,"type":"legacy_source"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=businesslink","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/brows